        <!-- Welcome Message -->
        <p>Dear Student,</p>
        <p>A warm welcome to ICFAI Business School Hyderabad.</p>
        <p>Congratulations on securing admission to the Two-year Full-Time Residential Program in Master’s in Business Administration (MBA) Batch of 2023-25 at ICFAI Business School (IBS) – Hyderabad.</p>
        <p>We are delighted to welcome and enroll you to our vibrant community of learners, and hopeful to see you transform into thought leaders. We believe that our world-class faculty, innovative curriculum, and state-of-the-art facilities will provide you with an unparalleled learning experience. We are committed to providing you an education that prepares you to meet the demands of the business world, and we are confident that you will find our program stimulating, rewarding, and fulfilling.</p>
        <p>Our state-of-the-art facilities are equipped with cutting-edge technology, and our faculty is well-versed in utilizing digital tools to deliver content in innovative and engaging ways. However, we also understand the value of human interaction and strive to blend technology judiciously with human intervention wherever required. Our goal is to provide you with a learning experience that is both high-tech and high-touch, enabling you to develop the skills and competencies needed to succeed in today's dynamic business landscape.</p>
        <p>As you settle in, we encourage you to take advantage of the numerous resources and opportunities available to you on campus. From networking events to career counseling services, we are here to support you at every step. We also expect you to make countless memories while you’re on campus. By counting the time in minutes, we encourage you to make the most of it. We expect you to eat healthy, stay peaceful, and think better.</p>
        <p>Once again, welcome to ICFAI Business School, Hyderabad. We look forward to meeting you, and we wish you all the best as you embark on this exciting journey.</p>
        <p><strong>Prof. K S Venugopal Rao</strong><br>Director, IBS Hyderabad</p>

